dct_description_sm: Topographical Section. General Staff Intelligence. Union Defense Force.

Maps of German South West Africa showing cities, towns, villages, rivers, roads, railways, stations, telegraph lines, pans, and other features in the regions of Otawi, Grootfontein, Swakopmund, Gobabis, Rehoboth, Arahoab, LÃ¼deritzbucht, Bethany, and Pomona.
Coordinates approxiate and based on Greenwhich meridian.
2 bar scales on map given in "Miles" and "Kilometres."
Includes compass rose, index map, and legend.
For 2 related maps, see German S. W. Africa : Sheet 20 Rehoboth [includes an index map different from this set] -- German S. W. Africa : Sheet 27 Pomona [dated 1915].
